calls.1_criteria_for_master_s_degree_programme:
The score for the students enrolled in a Master’s degree programme is determined based on the following criteria:
• Politecnico di Torino takes into consideration only the exam credits included in the StudyPlan which count towards the achievement of the degree and are validated by Politecnico di Torino;
• exams passed by the applicants but not validated are not counted (i.e., following a transfer);
• additional credits do not count towards the score (i.e., additional credits of Percorso Intraprendenti , Italian language credits for international students, traineeship extension credits, credits awarded following participation in special events/activities, etc.);
• in case of FULL TIME or PART-TIME enrolment for an entire academic year, the number of semesters of the career duration is set at 2;
• in case of an equal score on the ranking list, the younger applicant will be chosen;
• Politecnico di Torino takes into consideration the so called “integrated courses” ( corsi integrati ) exclusively if the student has taken all modules of the course, even if not registered in the transcript yet;
• pass-or-fail exams (exams without grade) are given the value of the average grade of other exams passed by the applicant up to the present.
Please note that for all courses/activities that can be recorded in the student transcript in a period of the year other than examination sessions (i.e., traineeship, external training activities…) Politecnico di Torino takes into consideration the actual registration date; therefore, if these activities are recorded after February 21, 2026 they are not considered for the score.
Students with a particularly complex university career are invited to contact the International Mobility Unit through the Ticketing Support System when they submit their application (topic “MOBILITÀ OUTGOING – TESI SU PROPOSTA”. Tickets sent after the deadlines for application submission will not be accepted for the calculation of the score.

calls.2_2_unregistered_exams:
Applicants who are waiting for the registration of some exams in their transcript when they submit their application must report this situation during the application phase using the online form that can be downloaded from the Bando Tesi su proposta website.
In particular Politecnico di Torino accepts self-declarations by:
• ongoing mobility students, or students who have completed a mobility project, students who have passed exams abroad by February 21, 2026, without having yet obtained the exam validation by Politecnico by the same date;
• students who have completed a mobility project, students who have passed exams abroad by February 21, 2026, and these exams have been validated by Politecnico di Torino at a later date;
• students who have passed exams at Politecnico di Torino by February 21, 2026, still waiting for the exam registration in the transcript by Politecnico by the same date.
The exams passed during a mobility project and self-certified by the student are assigned an evaluation (grade out of 30) equal to the weighted average of the other exams recorded in the student’s transcript by February 21, 2026.
In the self-declaration students must indicate:
• for exams taken during the mobility project: the number of credits of the corresponding exams provided in the study plan as set out in the last approved Learning Agreement;
• for exams passed at Politecnico di Torino that have not been registered in the transcript yet: course denomination, grade and exam date.

